 and then transfer some of its kinetic energy 

00:03:18.048 --> 00:03:20.521
 and then jump in that direction. 

00:03:20.521 --> 00:03:26.960
 While this, after the collision, 

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:31.560
 it may be moving much faster in that direction. 

00:03:31.560 --> 00:03:34.080
 And notice, you have a transfer of energy. 

00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:37.100
 Exactly with this collision you have a kinetic energy transfer 

00:03:37.100 --> 00:03:39.457
 of this molecule to this molecule. 

00:03:39.457 --> 00:03:41.791
 And it will happen in the system. 

00:03:41.791 --> 00:03:44.624
 Faster molecules, those with higher kinetic energy - 

00:03:44.624 --> 00:03:48.118
 while they collide, you will have an energy transfer. 

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:52.140
 You will have a transfer of energy from a higher temperature 

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:53.640
 to a lower temperature. 

00:03:53.820 --> 00:03:59.100
 Power transfer. 

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:01.120
 This is a transfer of energy. 

00:04:01.121 --> 00:04:03.525
 And you can accept this for the transfer of heat - 

00:04:03.525 --> 00:04:04.880
 here we talk about temperature. 

00:04:04.880 --> 00:04:07.220
 Things that are related to temperature, 

00:04:07.220 --> 00:04:08.720
 we will call it "thermal". 

00:04:08.720 --> 00:04:11.960
 This is a heat transfer. 

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:14.420
 Transfer of heat. 

00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:18.580
 If you start with higher energy here, 

00:04:18.580 --> 00:04:20.380
 you will have a higher average kinetic energy. 

00:04:20.382 --> 00:04:22.356
 Here you will have lower average kinetic energy. 

00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:27.600
 But it will transfer energy from the cyclamen to the blue. 

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:29.180
 This will go from a higher temperature 

00:04:29.183 --> 00:04:30.692
 to a lower temperature. 

00:04:30.700 --> 00:04:35.120
 And this energy, which is transferred, 

00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:39.520
 we call - and this is a word you probably hear many times - 

00:04:39.580 --> 00:04:43.620
 this energy that is transferred is called "heat". 

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:51.020
 Literally, this warmer gas here heats this cooler gas. 

00:04:51.020 --> 00:04:55.160
 And the way this heat transfer takes place, 

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:57.627
 when it is through a collision of particles, 

00:04:57.627 --> 00:05:01.140
 the transfer of kinetic energy to the collision of particles, 

00:05:01.140 --> 00:05:02.720
 who transfer the impulse, 

00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:05.060
 we call conducting. 

00:05:05.060 --> 00:05:07.720
 We call this heat (heat). 

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:09.780
 Or just conducting. 

