 It's a fire. 

00:05:57.880 --> 00:06:00.040
 And we talk about heating the metal on the pan, 

00:06:00.120 --> 00:06:02.515
 I'm not dealing with what's inside the pan right now. 

00:06:02.520 --> 00:06:07.260
 This fire will first heat the bottom of this saucepan. 

00:06:07.260 --> 00:06:11.180
 And it will do so mainly by thermal conduction, 

00:06:11.260 --> 00:06:14.380
 because the fire is just super hot air particles 

00:06:14.380 --> 00:06:15.980
 and these super hot air particles 

00:06:15.983 --> 00:06:19.083
 will hit the metal particles of your pan. 

00:06:19.083 --> 00:06:21.428
 These metal particles of this saucepan - 

00:06:21.428 --> 00:06:25.085
 their kinetic energy will begin to rise. 

00:06:25.085 --> 00:06:27.361
 This part of the pot will start to heat up. 

00:06:27.361 --> 00:06:30.820
 Just when you turn on your stove, 

00:06:30.820 --> 00:06:33.351
 the top of this saucepan may still be cold, 

00:06:33.351 --> 00:06:35.523
 but the bottom will quickly become very hot. 

00:06:35.523 --> 00:06:37.183
 But if you just wait a few minutes, 

00:06:37.183 --> 00:06:40.020
 these metal particles will continue to be pushed 

00:06:40.020 --> 00:06:41.840
 and vibrate to each other. 

00:06:41.850 --> 00:06:44.323
 And eventually, this upper part here 

00:06:44.323 --> 00:06:48.259
 it will be quite hot. 

00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:51.820
 It'll be pretty hot. 

00:06:51.820 --> 00:06:54.620
 And the way the top of this metal has become hot, 

00:06:54.621 --> 00:06:56.920
 is by heat conduction - 

00:06:56.920 --> 00:06:59.160
 first the metal on the bottom has become hot, 

00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:00.786
 then these particles have collided with their neighbors 

00:07:00.786 --> 00:07:02.284
 or have vibrated to their neighbors 

00:07:02.284 --> 00:07:04.060
 and have transferred some of this kinetic energy. 

00:07:04.060 --> 00:07:06.451
 And you see this heat transfer again 

00:07:06.460 --> 00:07:10.420
 from a higher temperature area 

00:07:10.420 --> 00:07:14.080
 to an area with a cooler or lower temperature. 

